340 g Turkey Breast Portions
2 unit(s) Sweet Potato
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
¼ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Zucchini
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
¼ tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Oil*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch rounds.
Combine panko, cheese and Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend in a shallow dish.
Pat turkey dry with paper towels, then, if applicable, cut into 2 (4) equal pieces on a separate cutting board.
Carefully slice into the centre of each turkey breast portion, lengthwise and parallel to the cutting board, leaving 1/2-inch intact on the other end.
Open up turkey like a book, then season both sides with salt and pepper.

Coat one side of each turkey breast portion with mayo.
Working with one breast at a time, firmly press mayo-coated side into panko mixture to adhere.
Transfer to a parchment-lined baking sheet, coated-side up.
Bake in the middle of the oven until cooked through, 18-20 min.**

Meanwhile, p eel, then cut sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add sweet potatoes, 1 tsp (2 tsp) salt and enough water to cover (by approx. 1-2 inches) to a large pot.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Once boiling, reduce heat to medium.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, until fork-tender, 10-12 min.

Add zucchini and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to an unlined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.
Roast, in the top of the oven until tender-crisp, 15-17 min

Drain and return sweet potatoes to the same pot, off heat.
Mash sour cream and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter into sweet potatoes until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

Divide sweet potato mash, cheddar-crusted turkey and zucchini between plates.

If you've opted to get turkey breast portions, pat turkey dry with paper towels, then, if applicable, cut into 2 (4) equal pieces on a separate cutting board. Carefully slice into the centre of each turkey breast portion, lengthwise and parallel to the cutting board, leaving 1/2-inch intact on the other end. Open up the turkey like a book, then season both sides with salt and pepper.

Coat one side of each turkey breast portion with mayo. Working with one breast at a time, firmly press mayo-coated side into panko mixture to adhere. Transfer to a parchment-lined baking sheet, coated-side up. Bake in the middle of the oven until cooked through, 18-20 min.**